<h2><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Matrix_(mathematics)&action=edit&section=32.php.html" title="Edit section: Notes">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Notes">Notes</span></h2>
<div class="reflist references-column-width" style="-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;">
<ol class="references">
<li id="cite_note-1"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-1">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">K.&#160;Bryan and T.&#160;Leise. The $25,000,000,000 eigenvector: The linear algebra behind Google. SIAM Review, 48(3):569–581, 2006.</span></li>
<li id="cite_note-2"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-2">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text">Brown&#160;<a href="#CITEREFBrown1991">1991</a>, Chapter I.1. Alternative references for this book include Lang&#160;<a href="#CITEREFLang1987b">1987b</a> and Greub&#160;<a href="#CITEREFGreub1975">1975</a></span></li>
